{"word":"εὐήθης","slug":"εὐήθης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐήθης</b></el> <el>(εὐ-ήθης, ες) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἦθος'><el>ἦθος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>good-hearted, open-hearted, simpleminded, guileless</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>τὸ εὔηθες  εὐήθεια</el>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>in bad sense, <i>simple, silly</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic: —as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> <i>a simpleton</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-θως</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <el>-έστερα</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>-έστατα</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}